DUBAI: Bahraini label Noon by Noor is returning to London Fashion Week (LFW) to present its upcoming fall 2022 collection on Feb. 19. For the latest updates, follow us on Instagram @arabnews.lifestyle The contemporary womenswear label, founded by cousins Shaikha Noor Al-Khalifa and Shaikha Haya Al-Khalifa in 2008, will showcase its offerings during an invite-only physical show that will kick off at 9:00 a.m.  A post shared by Noon By Noor (@noonbynoor) This will be the second time that the Bahraini brand, which typically shows during New York Fashion Week, participates in LFW. Noon by Noor staged a physical presentation for its Spring 2022 collection last September on Londonâ€™s schedule. Like the last few London Fashion Weeks, the upcoming event will be a physical-digital hybrid. The event will take place from Feb. 18-22.